Introduction

Youha (유하) is a South Korean singer-songwriter and composer currently under Universal Music Korea. She made her debut on September 29, 2020, with her digital single "Island".

She was first introduced as a member of the pre-debut team known as Future 2NE1 back in 2012, which was supposed to debut sometime in 2016. But for unknown reasons the debut was cancelled, so she continued the training process. She left YG Entertainment after 9 years of being a trainee under the label in 2019.

She wrote and produced VICTON's "What I Said", LOONA's "PTT (Paint The Town)", LOONA's "WOW" and "Not Friends" and wrote, produced and arranged My Teenage Girl's "Same Same Different", in addition to her own songs.
